main event: A report from Project Blue Book dated March 24, 1967, documenting photographs of structures and a train in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The report consists of multiple pages detailing black and white photographs without identifiable human faces., There are a total of 7 photographs described across the pages., The images show a distant row of buildings and a railway car., Some images exhibit atmospheric distortion and damage in quality., The document is classified as UNCLASSIFIED under the Foreign Technology Division, AFSC.
sighted object: black and white photographs of buildings and a railway car
